==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adulteress
<hw>A*dul"ter*ess</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Fem. from L.
<ets>adulter</ets>. Cf. <er>Advoutress</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
woman who commits adultery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Script.)</fld> <def>A woman who violates her
religious engagements.</def> <rj><au>James iv. 4.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adulterine</ent>⟦br⟧
